Defendant Willie Arthur Harrington Jr in court.  Attorney Douglas E. Batt in court for Willie Arthur Harrington Jr.  Prosecuting attorney Patrick T. Franken and Attorney Abby Rockendorf in court for the State of Wisconsin. 

Case in court for Final Pre-Trial. State motions for adjournment of Jury Trial.  Defense objects. For the reasons stated on the record, the Court finds good cause to adjourn the Jury Trial currently set for 10/10/2022.  Court sets the deadline of 12/8/2022 for filing of Jury Instructions, Motions in Limine, Witness lists and change of Plea forms. State to provide crime lab reports on or before the Final Pre-Trial hearing. Case adjourned to Br. 9.  Final pre-trial scheduled for December 15, 2022 at 10:00 am. Jury trial scheduled for January 3, 2023 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Willie Arthur Harrington in court with attorney Douglas E. Batt.  Alexander C. Dyer appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case in court for a pre-trial conference. Court was notified that defense has not received all of the discovery. Defense issued an oral motion to supress regarding the evidence that was not turned over to the defense. Court GRANTED the defenses motion to supress. Court ORDERS that all video evidence of a video from Saint Joseph's parking lot shall not be used at trial. Defense requested jury trial dates. Court set the following filing deadlines with parties. State has until August 5th, 2022, to submit any crime lab reports to the defense. Defense has until August 31st, 2022, to file any change of plea forms. Parties have until September 7th, 2022, to submit any trial documents. Case adjourned to Branch 17.
Pursuant to Chief Judge Directive 22-04, parties are hereby notified that effective 7/30/22, this case is assigned to branch 9, Judge Paul Van Grunsven in room 632 of the Courthouse.  Final pre-trial scheduled for September 14, 2022 at 10:30 am.  Jury trial scheduled for October 10, 2022 at 09:00 am.
